UNDIAGNOSED DEATHS, BOVINE - ZAMBIA: (SOUTHERN) REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
***********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 8 Dec 2017
Source: Lusaka Times [edited]
https://www.lusakatimes.com/2017/12/08/mysterious-cattle-disease-breaks-chikankata/


A mysterious cattle disease has broken out in Chikankata district in Southern province and has since claimed 7 head of cattle.

Chikankata District Veterinary Officer Dr Abraham Msoni has disclosed that his office has since dispatched a team of officers to verify the reported outbreak of the peculiar cattle disease, which has so far claimed 7 head of cattle in Chikankata.

Dr Msoni told ZANIS yesterday [7 Dec 2017] in Chikankata that his officers are currently ascertaining the type of disease that has broken out in the district and further called on farmers to report cases of animal diseases on time so that their animals are attended to as quickly as possible.

One affected farmer interviewed by the Zambia News and Information Services in Chikankata district yesterday [7 Dec 2017] said he had lost 2 animals within a week. He added that his animals just collapsed, and within a short period, the animals lost their lives.

He wondered what type of disease this was since it did not show signs of the corridor disease popularly known as Denkete in Tonga.

Another farmer said the disease kills cattle quickly and has called on the Ministry of Fisheries and Livestock to immediately move in to prevent more animals from dying. He had lost 5 animals within a period of 2 weeks and said that quick efforts should be put in place by the ministry so that the disease is contained.

